  "prompt": "Why is the Duronto train green?",
  "response": "The color of the Duronto trains, which is a bright green, is primarily a branding choice by Indian Railways. This specific coloring distinguishes the Duronto Express trains from other trains and makes them easily recognizable. The design and color scheme for the Duronto express trains were intended to give a fresh and vibrant look, symbolizing speed and agility, as these are non-stop, long-distance trains that aim to reduce travel time between major cities. Additionally, the green color may symbolize environmental consciousness and energy efficiency, although the primary reasons remain centered around brand identity and aesthetic appeal.",
